  "text": "After these parameters are determined, we demonstrate that the strain with suboptimal reproduction number dominates in Figure 5 . In Figure 5 we have the reproduction number of strain one, R 1 = 2.00, while the reproduction number of strain two, R 2 = 2.51. Yet, strain one, represented by I(t), is the dominant strain, while strain two, represented by J(t), is eliminated. Therefore, the principle that the strain with higher reproduction number excludes the strain with lower reproduction number is not valid in this model [CITATION_1] .",
